{"id": 3826, "title": "Ticket #3826: Is COLLECTOR_HOST a list?", "description": "<blockquote>\n<a class=\"external\" href=\"http://research.cs.wisc.edu/htcondor/manual/v8.0/3_3Configuration.html#16713\">http://research.cs.wisc.edu/htcondor/manual/v8.0/3_3Configuration.html#16713</a>\n\n<p>does not mention if COLLECTOR_HOST is a list.\n\n</p><p><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://research.cs.wisc.edu/htcondor/manual/v8.0/3_3Configuration.html#18745\">http://research.cs.wisc.edu/htcondor/manual/v8.0/3_3Configuration.html#18745</a>\n\n</p><p>defines a macro removed in HTCondor 6.9.3 and mentions in passing that COLLECTOR_HOST may be a list.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2014-Mar-06 10:56:45 by smoler:</em> <br/>\n\nYes, <code>COLLECTOR_HOST</code> can be a comma separated list.  With multiple collectors running, updates are sent to all of them; queries go to one chosen at random.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=3936\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('3936'); return false;\" title=\"COLLECTOR_HOST accepts a list of addresses, not just one.\">#3936</a></span></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon ptr1\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\nCOLLECTOR_HOST accepts a list of addresses, not just one.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Mar-06 10:58</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/f7b746bf9bc371ed9f6dc4a59ec9f4b091498516\">[39540]</a></span>: COLLECTOR_HOST can be a comma separated list. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=3826\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('3826'); return false;\" title=\"Is COLLECTOR_HOST a list?\">#3826</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "doc", "last_change": "2014-Mar-06 11:01", "status": "resolved", "created": "2013-Jul-30 16:05", "fixed_version": "2013-Jul-30 16:05", "broken_version": "", "priority": "4", "subsystem": "", "assigned_to": "smoler", "derived_from": "", "creator": "tlmiller", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "notify": "", "due_date": ""}